Welcome to Acme.  

Right click on manual references, e.g., intro(1) or acme(1), 
to read a manual page. You should read acme(1) before 
using this editor.

Drag the mouse while holding down the middle mouse 
button to execute some text, e.g.,

	lookman intro

Right-click on pathnames to open a window on the 
file or directory, e.g. 
	/appl/acme

Change the acme namespace by prefixing mount and 
bind commands with 'Local'. Mount the plan9 source for 
browsing by middle-selecting this text then right-click 
the pathname /n/sources.

	Local mount -A tcp!sources.cs.bell-labs.com!9fs /n/sources

Read and edit the Inferno wiki,

	Local mount -A tcp!canto.hopto.org!wiki /mnt/wiki
	Wiki

Join other inferno users on #inferno IRC channel,

	airc -n acmeuser irc.freenode.net

You'll probably want to work on files in your host system,

	Local bind -c '#UC:/' /n/c
	Local bind -c '#UD:/' /n/d

Browse the web: middle-click on the command 

	charon 

then right-click on words that have a superscript number.
